Nominal Accounts Appear here mostly

Income = Revenue - COGS 

Income increases equity .... credit income

revenue - cost of goods sold = gross profit

operating income= gross profit - operating expenses (opex)

profit before tax =  operating income + other income - other expenses

net income = profit after tax = pbt - taxes

EBIT: earnings before income tax --> operating income

EBITDA: earnings  before income tax depreciation and amortization --> d and a  are added back to operating profit, as they are eliminated in operating expenses

EBITDA >> EBIT